# INSTALL -- gui-mcp build, install, and update

## Prerequisites

- Windows 10/11 with a live desktop session (not headless)
- Rust stable toolchain (rustup.rs)
- Git
- A live desktop session (required for window capture and input injection)

## First-time install

### 1. Clone and build

```
git clone https://github.com/lpmwfx/gui-mcp.git
cd gui-mcp
cargo build --release
```

### 2. Install binary

Copy the release binary to a location on your PATH:

```
cp target/release/slint-gui-mcp.exe ~/bin/gui-mcp.exe
```

The binary is self-contained -- no runtime dependencies, no DLLs.

### 3. Configure MCP client

#### Claude Code

Add to `~/.claude/settings.json` under `mcpServers`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "gui-mcp": {
      "command": "C:/Users/YOU/bin/gui-mcp.exe",
      "args": [],
      "type": "stdio"
    }
  }
}
```

Replace `YOU` with your Windows username.

#### Codex

Add to your Codex MCP config:

```json
{
  "gui-mcp": {
    "command": "C:/Users/YOU/bin/gui-mcp.exe",
    "args": []
  }
}
```

### 4. Verify

Start a new Claude Code session and run:

```
list_windows()
```

If it returns a list of window titles, the server is working.

## Update

### Quick update (same session)

When you rebuild gui-mcp during development:

```
cd gui-mcp
cargo build --release
taskkill //IM gui-mcp.exe //F
cp target/release/slint-gui-mcp.exe ~/bin/gui-mcp.exe
```

Then restart the Claude Code session (or use `/mcp` to reconnect).

The `taskkill` step is required because the running MCP server locks the exe file.
On Windows, the MCP server process is managed by the MCP client (Claude Code) and
will be restarted automatically on the next tool call after session restart.

### Pull and update

```
cd gui-mcp
git pull
cargo build --release
taskkill //IM gui-mcp.exe //F
cp target/release/slint-gui-mcp.exe ~/bin/gui-mcp.exe
```

Restart the Claude Code session to pick up the new binary.

### Verify the update

After restarting the session:

```
help()
```

The help tool shows the current tool count and available topics.
Check that the tool count matches what you expect after the update.

## Paths

| What | Path |
|------|------|
| Source repo | `D:\REPO\RUSTPROJECTS\MCP\gui-mcp` |
| Release binary | `target\release\slint-gui-mcp.exe` |
| Installed binary | `C:\Users\mathi\bin\gui-mcp.exe` |
| MCP config | `C:\Users\mathi\.claude\settings.json` |

## Troubleshooting

### "cannot create regular file: Device or resource busy"

The MCP server is still running. Kill it first:

```
taskkill //IM gui-mcp.exe //F
```

### MCP tools not available after update

Restart the Claude Code session. The MCP server is spawned per-session.

### Tool calls return errors about missing windows

Ensure you have a live desktop session. gui-mcp uses Win32 HWND capture
which requires a visible desktop -- it cannot work in headless/RDP shadow mode.

### DPI / coordinate mismatch

gui-mcp declares DPI awareness at process startup. If coordinates drift,
check that the target window is on the primary monitor and that Windows
display scaling is consistent.
